# Performance Conventions

## Route-level code splitting

```tsx
// apps/*/src/app/routes.tsx
const HomePage = lazy(() => import("@/pages/HomePage"));

{
  path: "/",
  element: (
    <Suspense fallback={<PageSkeleton />}>
      <HomePage />
    </Suspense>
  ),
}
```

- Put `Suspense` boundary at layout or route level
- Provide lightweight skeleton fallback (not blank screen)

## Images

- Use native `<img>` with `loading="lazy"` for below-fold content
- Always set `width`/`height` or aspect ratio to prevent CLS
- Prefer responsive `srcSet` for hero images when added
- Future shared `Image` component → `packages/ui` if needed across apps

## Bundles

- Import workspace packages by subpath (`@ryx/ui/components/ui/button`)
- Avoid barrel imports that pull unused components
